    narr:narration """This hub collects per-document **novelty assessments** for a rubric dimension scoring originality of framing and language. The mainline finding is consistent across artifacts: fresh, distinctive framing that avoids startup cliché. Recurring praise lands on coined metaphors — [continuation-machines / substrate framing](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty), [code-as-compilation-output](narr:Rubric_Assess_Novelty) and its [worldview-vs-skills echo](narr:Rubric_Novelty_YC_Call), [Gods of Olympus / ambient adoption](narr:Rubric_Novelty_FounderBetaUser), the [conviction taxonomy in the YC assessment](narr:Assessment_Novelty_YC), and [AI-to-AI provenance insight](narr:Rubric_Novelty_CustomerArchitect). Several note quantified lexical diversity (type-token ~0.67-0.68). Assessments span pitch/bio material ([Scarlet bio](narr:Rubric_Novelty_ScarletDame)), GTM and revenue docs ([revenue/TAM](narr:Assess_Novelty_RevenueModelTAM), [GTM](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_GTM)), call notes ([weekly call](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_WeeklyCall)), and pilot/demo plans ([pilot plan](narr:Rubric_Novelty_PilotPlan), [YC demo beats](narr:Rubric_Novelty_YCDemoBeats)). The grades cluster high-originality, but the children are not uniform — most flag a freshness-vs-boilerplate seam, and one carries no assessment at all.""" ;
